1.00	S%C3%A1ndor_Iharos	Sándor Iharos	Sándor Iharos (March 10, 1930 – January 24, 1996) was a Hungarian distance runner. Though unsuccessful in major competitions, Iharos ran world records over multiple distances and is one of only two athletes (the other being nine-time Olympic champion Paavo Nurmi) to have held outdoor world records over 1500 metres, 5000 metres and 10000 metres. Iharos was one of the star pupils of the famous coach Mihály Iglói.	
